<dl id="s14040c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14040c">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s14all.htm#s14040c">sector 40(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> revile the living <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="s14040c"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/lexp.htm#s14040c">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/p86.htm#s14040c">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/p86.htm#s14040c">1986 (14.824)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/l22p.htm#s14040c">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#s14040c">MS V.A.17-7</ms> </li><li>JJA 14:109 </li><li><a name="p12d" href="../udra/u14da.htm#p12d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/p12d.htm#s14040c">Draft: 14.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">These answerers have no other employment but to cry out Dunce and Scribbler, to praise the dead, and <mark>revile the living</mark>; to grant a man of confessed abilities some small share of merit; to applaud twenty blockheads, in order to gain the reputation of candour; and to revile the moral character of the man whose writings they cannot injure. <small> Oliver Goldsmith, <a name="OGCW" href="/udra/udex.htm#OGCW"><cite title="source">Complete Works</cite></a> (n.d), <i>Citizen of the World</i>, p 422</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
